question: Among the schools with an SAT excellence rate of over 0.3, what is the highest eligible free rate for students aged 5-17?
evidence: Excellence rate = NumGE1500 / NumTstTakr; Eligible free rates for students aged 5-17 = `Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` / `Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`
SQL: SELECT MAX(CAST(T1.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` AS REAL) / T1.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE CAST(T2.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / T2.NumTstTakr > 0.3

SELECT MAX(T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free.content: SELECT MAX(T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)`) FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE CAST(T1.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / T1.NumTstTakr > 0.3

SELECT Percent__Eligible_Free__Ages_5_17.content: SELECT Percent__Eligible_Free__Ages_5_17 FROM frpm WHERE CDSCode IN ( SELECT cds FROM satscores WHERE CAST(NumGE1500 AS REAL) / NumTstTakr  >  0.3 ) ORDER BY Percent__Eligible_Free__Ages_5_17 DESC LIMIT 1

SELECT MAX(T1.`Percent (%) Eligible Free.content: SELECT MAX(T1.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)`) FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE CAST(T2.NumGE1500 AS REAL) * 1.0 / T2.NumTstTakr > 0.3

question: Name schools in Riverside which the average of average math score for SAT is grater than 400, what is the funding type of these schools?
evidence: Average of average math = sum(average math scores) / count(schools).
SQL: SELECT T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.`District Name` LIKE 'Riverside%' GROUP BY T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` HAVING CAST(SUM(T1.AvgScrMath) AS REAL) / COUNT(T1.cds) > 400

question: State the names and full communication address of high schools in Monterey which has more than 800 free or reduced price meals for ages 15-17?

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.

SQL: SELECT MAX(CAST(T1.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` AS REAL) / T1.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE CAST(T2.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / T2.NumTstTakr > 0.3

SELECT MAX(T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free.content: SELECT MAX(T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)`) FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE CAST(T1.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / T1.NumTstTakr > 0.3
SELECT MAX(T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)`) FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE CAST(T1.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / NumTstTakr > 0.3

SELECT T3.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ag.content: SELECT T3.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode INNER JOIN frpm AS T3 ON T2.CDSCode = T3.CDSCode WHERE T1.NumGE1500 / T1.NumTstTakr > 0.3 ORDER BY T3.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` DESC LIMIT 1

SELECT T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ag.content: SELECT T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE CAST(T1.NumGE1500 AS REAL) * 100 / T1.NumTstTakr > 30 ORDER BY T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` DESC LIMIT 1

SELECT frpm.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (.content: SELECT frpm.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` FROM frpm INNER JOIN satscores ON frpm.CDSCode = satscores.cds WHERE CAST(satscores.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / satscores.NumTstTakr > 0.3 ORDER BY frpm.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` DESC LIMIT 1

SELECT T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ag.content: SELECT T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE CAST(T1.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / T1.NumTstTakr > 0.3 ORDER BY T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` DESC LIMIT 1

SELECT T1.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ag.content: SELECT T1.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE CAST(T2.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / T2.NumTstTakr > 0.3 ORDER BY T1.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)` DESC LIMIT 1

SELECT MAX(T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free.content: SELECT MAX(T2.`Percent (%) Eligible Free (Ages 5-17)`) FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE CAST(T1.NumGE1500 AS REAL) * 100 / T1.NumTstTakr > 30

SELECT T1.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)`.content: SELECT T1.`Free Meal Count (Ages 5-17)` / T1.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)` AS a FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE CAST(T2.NumGE1500 AS REAL) / T2.NumTstTakr > 0.3 ORDER BY a DESC LIMIT 1

question: Rank schools by their average score in Writing where the score is greater than 499, showing their charter numbers.
evidence: Valid charter number means the number is not null
SQL: SELECT CharterNum, AvgScrWrite, RANK() OVER (ORDER BY AvgScrWrite DESC) AS WritingScoreRank FROM schools AS T1  INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE T2.AvgScrWrite > 499 AND CharterNum is not null

SELECT T1.CharterNum FROM schools AS T1.content: SELECT T1.CharterNum FROM schools AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE T2.AvgScrWrite > 499 ORDER BY T2.AvgScrWrite DESC

SELECT T2.AvgScrWrite, T1.CharterNum FRO.content: SELECT T2.AvgScrWrite, T1.CharterNum FROM schools AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE T2.AvgScrWrite > 499 ORDER BY T2.AvgScrWrite DESC

question: List the names of schools with more than 30 difference in enrollements between K-12 and ages 5-17? Please also give the full street adress of the schools.

question: Give the names of the schools with the percent eligible for free meals in K-12 is more than 0.1 and test takers whose test score is greater than or equal to 1500?
evidence: Percent eligible for free meals = Free Meal Count (K-12) / Total (Enrollment (K-12)

question: Name schools in Riverside which the average of average math score for SAT is grater than 400, what is the funding type of these schools?
evidence: Average of average math = sum(average math scores) / count(schools).
SQL: SELECT T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.`District Name` LIKE 'Riverside%' GROUP BY T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` HAVING CAST(SUM(T1.AvgScrMath) AS REAL) / COUNT(T1.cds) > 400

SELECT T1.FundingType FROM schools AS T1.content: SELECT T1.FundingType FROM schools AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE T1.County = 'Riverside' GROUP BY T1.County HAVING SUM(T2.AvgScrMath) / COUNT(T2.cds) > 400

SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.School), T1.Fun.content: SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT T1.School), T1.FundingType FROM schools AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE T1.County = 'Riverside' GROUP BY T1.School HAVING AVG(T2.AvgScrMath) > 400

SELECT DISTINCT T1.School, T1.FundingTyp.content: SELECT DISTINCT T1.School, T1.FundingType FROM schools AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE T1.County = 'Riverside' GROUP BY T1.School HAVING SUM(T2.AvgScrMath) / COUNT(T1.School) > 400

SELECT T2.fundingtype FROM satscores AS.content: SELECT T2.fundingtype FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.County = 'Riverside' GROUP BY T2.School HAVING AVG(T1.AvgScrMath) > 400

question: State the names and full communication address of high schools in Monterey which has more than 800 free or reduced price meals for ages 15-17?

question: What is the average score in writing for the schools that were opened after 1991 or closed before 2000? List the school names along with the score. Also, list the communication number of the schools if there is any.

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.

question: What is the eligible free rate of the 10th and 11th schools with the highest enrolment for students in grades 1 through 12?
evidence: K-12 refers to students in grades 1 through 12; Eligible free rate for K-12 = `Free Meal Count (K-12)` / `Enrollment (K-12)`

SELECT s.School, s.County, ss.AvgScrRead.content:
SELECT s.School, s.County, ss.AvgScrRead
FROM schools s
JOIN satscores ss ON s.CDSCode = ss.cds
WHERE s.Virtual = 'F'
AND s.School IN (
    SELECT School
    FROM (
        SELECT s.School, s.County, ss.AvgScrRead,
               RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY s.County ORDER BY ss.AvgScrRead DESC) as ranking
        FROM schools s
        JOIN satscores ss ON s.CDSCode = ss.cds
        WHERE s.Virtual = 'F'
    ) ranked
    WHERE ranking <= 5
)

question: Between San Diego and Santa Barbara, which county offers the most number of schools that does not offer physical building? Indicate the amount.
evidence: 'Does not offer physical building' means Virtual = F in the database.
SQL: SELECT County, COUNT(Virtual) FROM schools WHERE (County = 'San Diego' OR County = 'Santa Barbara') AND Virtual = 'F' GROUP BY County ORDER BY COUNT(Virtual) DESC LIMIT 1

question: Of the schools that offers a magnet program serving a grade span of Kindergarten to 8th grade, how many offers Multiple Provision Types? List the number of cities that offers a Kindergarten to 8th grade span and indicate how many schools are there serving such grade span for each city.

question: What is the Percent (%) Eligible Free (K-12) in the school administered by an administrator whose first name is Alusine. List the district code of the school.

question: Among the schools with an SAT excellence rate of over 0.3, what is the highest eligible free rate for students aged 5-17?

question: Name schools in Riverside which the average of average math score for SAT is grater than 400, what is the funding type of these schools?
evidence: Average of average math = sum(average math scores) / count(schools).
SQL: SELECT T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.`District Name` LIKE 'Riverside%' GROUP BY T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` HAVING CAST(SUM(T1.AvgScrMath) AS REAL) / COUNT(T1.cds) > 400

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.

SQL: SELECT T2.AdmFName1, T2.AdmLName1, T2.AdmFName2, T2.AdmLName2, T2.AdmFName3, T2.AdmLName3 FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode ORDER BY T1.NumGE1500 DESC LIMIT 1

SELECT T2.AdmFName1, T2.AdmLName1, T2.AdmFName2, T2.AdmLName2, T2.AdmFName3, T2.AdmLName3 FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode ORDER BY T1.NumGE1500 DESC LIMIT 1

question: List the names of virtual schools that are among the top 5 in their respective counties based on average reading scores.
evidence: Exclusively virtual refers to Virtual = 'F'; respective counties means PARTITION BY County
SQL: SELECT School FROM (SELECT T2.School,T1.AvgScrRead, RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY T2.County ORDER BY T1.AvgScrRead DESC) AS rnk FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.Virtual = 'F' ) ranked_schools WHERE rnk <= 5

SELECT T1.School FROM schools AS T1 INNE.content: SELECT T1.School FROM schools AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE T1.Virtual = 'F' ORDER BY T1.County, T2.AvgScrRead DESC GROUP BY T1.County LIMIT 5

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.

question: What is the complete address of the school with the lowest excellence rate? Indicate the Street, City, Zip and State.

question: Under whose administration is the school with the highest number of students scoring 1500 or more on the SAT? Indicate their full names.

question: What is the average number of test takers from Fresno schools that opened between 1/1/1980 and 12/31/1980?
evidence: between 1/1/1980 and 12/31/1980 means the year = 1980
SQL: SELECT AVG(T1.NumTstTakr) FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE strftime('%Y', T2.OpenDate) = '1980' AND T2.County = 'Fresno'

question: List the names of virtual schools that are among the top 5 in their respective counties based on average reading scores.
evidence: Exclusively virtual refers to Virtual = 'F'; respective counties means PARTITION BY County
SQL: SELECT School FROM (SELECT T2.School,T1.AvgScrRead, RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY T2.County ORDER BY T1.AvgScrRead DESC) AS rnk FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.Virtual = 'F' ) ranked_schools WHERE rnk <= 5

SELECT T1.school FROM schools AS T1 INNE.content: SELECT T1.school FROM schools AS T1 INNER JOIN satscores AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.cds WHERE T1.Virtual = 'F' GROUP BY T1.CDSCode ORDER BY T2.AvgScrRead DESC LIMIT 5

SELECT s.School, s.County, sc.AvgScrRead.content:
SELECT s.School, s.County, sc.AvgScrRead, 
       RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY s.County ORDER BY sc.AvgScrRead DESC) as Rank
FROM schools s
JOIN satscores sc ON s.CDSCode = sc.cds
WHERE s.Virtual = 'F'
AND s.NCESDist IS NOT NULL
ORDER BY s.County, sc.AvgScrRead DESC

SELECT s.School, s.County, ss.AvgScrRead.content:
SELECT s.School, s.County, ss.AvgScrRead
FROM schools s
JOIN satscores ss ON s.CDSCode = ss.cds

ORDER BY s.County, ss.AvgScrRead DESC
LIMIT 5 PER GROUP (s.County)

question: Name schools in Riverside which the average of average math score for SAT is grater than 400, what is the funding type of these schools?
evidence: Average of average math = sum(average math scores) / count(schools).

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.
evidence: Difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment can be computed by `Enrollment (K-12)` - `Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`
SQL: SELECT T2.School, T2.DOC FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.FundingType = 'Locally funded' AND (T1.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T1.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) > (SELECT AVG(T3.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T3.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) FROM frpm AS T3 INNER JOIN schools AS T4 ON T3.CDSCode = T4.CDSCode WHERE T4.FundingType = 'Locally funded')

WHERE T1.FundingType = 'Locally funded' 
AND T2.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T2.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)` > (
    SELECT AVG(T2.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T2.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) 
    FROM schools AS T1 
    JOIN frpm AS T2 
    ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode 
    WHERE T1.FundingType = 'Locally funded'
)

SELECT s.School, s.County, avgs.AvgScrRe.content:
SELECT s.School, s.County, avgs.AvgScrRead
FROM schools s
JOIN (
    SELECT cds, County, AVG(AvgScrRead) AS AvgScrRead
    FROM (
        SELECT cds, County, AvgScrRead,
               ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY County ORDER BY AvgScrRead DESC) as rank
        FROM satscores
    ) 
    WHERE rank <= 5
    GROUP BY cds, County
) avgs ON s.CDSCode = avgs.cds

SELECT S.school, S.County, R.AvgScrRead.content:
SELECT S.school, S.County, R.AvgScrRead 
FROM schools S 
JOIN satscores R 
ON S.CDSCode = R.cds 
WHERE S.Virtual = 'F' 
AND (S.County, R.AvgScrRead) IN (
    SELECT County, AvgScrRead 
    FROM (
        SELECT County, AvgScrRead, 
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY County ORDER BY AvgScrRead DESC) as rn
        FROM schools S 
        JOIN satscores R 
        ON S.CDSCode = R.cds 
        WHERE S.Virtual = 'F'
    ) 
    WHERE rn <= 5
) 
GROUP BY S.school, S.County, R.AvgScrRead 
ORDER BY S.County, R.AvgScrRead DESC

question: Name schools in Riverside which the average of average math score for SAT is grater than 400, what is the funding type of these schools?
evidence: Average of average math = sum(average math scores) / count(schools).
SQL: SELECT T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.`District Name` LIKE 'Riverside%' GROUP BY T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` HAVING CAST(SUM(T1.AvgScrMath) AS REAL) / COUNT(T1.cds) > 400

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.
evidence: Difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment can be computed by `Enrollment (K-12)` - `Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`

question: State the names and full communication address of high schools in Monterey which has more than 800 free or reduced price meals for ages 15-17?

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.

question: List the names of virtual schools that are among the top 5 in their respective counties based on average reading scores.
evidence: Exclusively virtual refers to Virtual = 'F'; respective counties means PARTITION BY County
SQL: SELECT School FROM (SELECT T2.School,T1.AvgScrRead, RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY T2.County ORDER BY T1.AvgScrRead DESC) AS rnk FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.Virtual = 'F' ) ranked_schools WHERE rnk <= 5

FROM (

SELECT DISTINCT s.School\nFROM schools s.content:
SELECT DISTINCT s.School
FROM schools s
JOIN satscores ss ON s.CDSCode = ss.cds
WHERE s.Virtual = 'V'
AND (s.County, ss.AvgScrRead) IN (
    SELECT County, MAX(AvgScrRead)
    FROM schools s2
    JOIN satscores ss2 ON s2.CDSCode = ss2.cds
    WHERE s2.Virtual = 'V'
    GROUP BY County
    UNION ALL
    SELECT County, MAX(AvgScrRead)
    FROM (
        SELECT County, AvgScrRead,
               ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY County ORDER BY AvgScrRead DESC) as rn
        FROM schools s2
        JOIN satscores ss2 ON s2.CDSCode = ss2.cds
        WHERE s2.Virtual = 'V'
        ORDER BY County, rn
    ) sub
    WHERE rn IN (2, 3, 4, 5)
)

SQL: SELECT T2.City, COUNT(T2.CDSCode) FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.Magnet = 1 AND T2.GSoffered = 'K-8' AND T1.`NSLP Provision Status` = 'Multiple Provision Types' GROUP BY T2.City

SELECT City, COUNT(CDSCode) AS NumberOfSchools 
FROM schools 
WHERE Magnet = 1 AND GSserved = 'K-8' AND CDSCode IN (
    SELECT CDSCode 
    FROM frpm 
    WHERE `NSLP Provision Status` = 'Multiple Provision Types'
) 
GROUP BY City

    SELECT CDSCode

) 
GROUP BY City

question: Name schools in Riverside which the average of average math score for SAT is grater than 400, what is the funding type of these schools?

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.
evidence: Difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment can be computed by `Enrollment (K-12)` - `Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`
SQL: SELECT T2.School, T2.DOC FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.FundingType = 'Locally funded' AND (T1.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T1.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) > (SELECT AVG(T3.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T3.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) FROM frpm AS T3 INNER JOIN schools AS T4 ON T3.CDSCode = T4.CDSCode WHERE T4.FundingType = 'Locally funded')

question: What are the valid e-mail addresses of the administrator of the school located in the San Bernardino county, City of San Bernardino City Unified that opened between 1/1/2009 to 12/31/2010 whose school types are public Intermediate/Middle Schools and Unified Schools?

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.
evidence: Difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment can be computed by `Enrollment (K-12)` - `Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`
SQL: SELECT T2.School, T2.DOC FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.FundingType = 'Locally funded' AND (T1.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T1.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) > (SELECT AVG(T3.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T3.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) FROM frpm AS T3 INNER JOIN schools AS T4 ON T3.CDSCode = T4.CDSCode WHERE T4.FundingType = 'Locally funded')

question: Name schools in Riverside which the average of average math score for SAT is grater than 400, what is the funding type of these schools?
evidence: Average of average math = sum(average math scores) / count(schools).
SQL: SELECT T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` FROM satscores AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.cds = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.`District Name` LIKE 'Riverside%' GROUP BY T1.sname, T2.`Charter Funding Type` HAVING CAST(SUM(T1.AvgScrMath) AS REAL) / COUNT(T1.cds) > 400

question: Consider the average difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment of schools that are locally funded, list the names and DOC type of schools which has a difference above this average.
evidence: Difference between K-12 enrollment and 15-17 enrollment can be computed by `Enrollment (K-12)` - `Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`
SQL: SELECT T2.School, T2.DOC FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.FundingType = 'Locally funded' AND (T1.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T1.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) > (SELECT AVG(T3.`Enrollment (K-12)` - T3.`Enrollment (Ages 5-17)`) FROM frpm AS T3 INNER JOIN schools AS T4 ON T3.CDSCode = T4.CDSCode WHERE T4.FundingType = 'Locally funded')

SELECT T1.School, T1.DOCType FROM school.content: SELECT T1.School, T1.DOCType FROM schools AS T1 INNER JOIN frpm AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.`Percent (%) Eligible FRPM (K-12)` - T2.`Percent (%) Eligible FRPM (Ages 5-17)` > ( SELECT AVG(`Percent (%) Eligible FRPM (K-12)` - `Percent (%) Eligible FRPM (Ages 5-17)`) FROM frpm ) AND T1.FundingType = 'Directly funded'

SELECT AVG(T1.\"Enrollment (K-12)\" - T1.content: SELECT AVG(T1."Enrollment (K-12)" - T1."Enrollment (Ages 5-17)") AS avg_diff FROM frpm AS T1 INNER JOIN schools AS T2 ON T1.CDSCode = T2.CDSCode WHERE T2.FundingType = 'Locally funded'
